div.p: Recent versions of draw.io include an automatic dark mode, which converts diagrams created in the light theme to dark. This can cause inconsistencies on websites (such as those built with Docusaurus) that have their own dark mode, since the colors may not match your corporate identity (CI).
To ensure that only your defined dark-mode colors are used, follow these steps:

ol.li:
In the color picker, click
Advanced
(1).
Next to the moon icon, define the color for dark mode.

In the dropdown on the right, select
User-defined
.

div.p:
Additionally, you can preload your style guide’s colors (both light and dark) in the color selection panel by copying and pasting the provided code into
Extras > Configuration...
, then reloading draw.io.

Note:
This does not currently work in the Mac OS desktop app but works in the browser version of draw.io.
